    "last_activity_date" : 1450733852,
    "creation_date" : 1450733852,
    "answer_id" : 34404745,
    "question_id" : 33483697,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had the same issue. The problem is that the Spring Boot annotation processor generates the <code>spring-configuration-metadata.json</code> file inside your <code>/target/classes/META-INF</code> folder.</p>\n\n<p>If you happen to have ignored this folder in IntelliJ like me (because what the heck, who cares about classes files?), the file won't be indexed by your IDE. Therefore, no completion, and the annoying message.</p>\n\n<p>Just remove <code>target</code> from the ignore files/folders list, located in <code>Settings &gt; Editor &gt; File Types &gt; Ignore files and folders</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
